OL,3,CJSO ruling sets precedent for harsher
OL,4,Csentencing of protesters, barrister
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FA leading human-rights lawyer has told
OL,8,FITV News that a Court of Appeal ruling
OL,9,Fon the sentences of 16 Just Stop Oil
OL,10,F(JSO) activists has set a precedent
OL,11,Ffor non-violent protesters to receive
OL,12,Ftougher penalties in the future.
OL,14,FJohn Cooper KC, told ITV News that the
OL,15,Fsentences handed to many of the
OL,16,Fenvironmental group's members were
OL,17,Fusually reserved for protests which
OL,18,F"involved violence", which did not
OL,19,Fapply in these cases.
