OL,3,CJSO ruling sets precedent for harsher
OL,4,Csentencing of protesters, barrister
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FWhile Hallam's sentence was reduced
OL,8,Ffrom five to four years, 10 of the 16
OL,9,Fprotesters' appeals were dismissed by
OL,10,Fthe appeal court, with lawyers for JSO
OL,11,Fsaying they were "considering" taking
OL,12,Fthe case to the Supreme Court.
OL,14,FCooper said this case is "important"
OL,15,Fas it is means the court has put down
OL,16,Fa "marker", effectively increasing
OL,17,Fsentencing powers for cases centred
OL,18,Faround demonstrations, although he
OL,19,Fthinks these tougher sentences would
OL,20,Fmainly be reserved for the "higher
OL,21,Fechelons" of protest groups.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
